t%20ruled%20that%20election%20commissioners%20must%20be%20appointed%20on%20the%20advice%20of%20a%20panel%20comprising%20the%20Prime%20Minister%2C%20the%20Leader%20of%20Opposition%20and%20the%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20India.%20The%20landmark%20judgment%20was%20aimed%20at%20insulating%20the%20top%20election%20body%20from%20political%20interference.%20The%20court%2C%20however%2C%20held%20that%20the%20judgment%20will%20hold%20good%20till%20government%20comes%20up%20with%20a%20law.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20new%20legislation%2C%20the%20government%20replaced%20the%20Chief%20Justice%20with%20a%20Union%20Minister.%20This%2C%20the%20Opposition%20has%20alleged%2C%20gives%20the%20government%20greater%20powers%20on%20the%20appointment%20of%20top%20poll%20officers%20and%20compromises%20the%20autonomy%20of%20the%20poll%20body.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20discussion%20the%20Bill%20in%20Rajya%20Sabha%2C%20Congress%20MP%20Randeep%20Surjewala%20said%20the%20autonomy%2C%20fearlessness%20and%20fairness%20of%20India's%20democracy%20and%20electoral%20machinery%20have%20been%20crushed%20by%20a%20bulldozer.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BModi%20government%20has%20attacked%20the%20democracy%20of%20India.%20The%20autonomy%2C%20fearlessness%20and%20fairness%20of%20India's%20democracy%20and%20electoral%20machinery%20have%20been%20crushed%20by%20a%20bulldozer%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnother%20point%20in%20the%20Bill%20that%20had%20drawn%20protests%20from%20former%20poll%20officers%20was%20a%20proposal%20to%20strip%20the%20Chief%20Election%20Commissioner%20and%20other%20Election%20Commissioners%20of%20the%20status%20of%20Supreme%20Court%20judges%2C%20and%20bring%20their%20salary%20and%20rank%20on%20par%20with%20an%20officer%20of%20Cabinet%20Secretary-rank.%20The%20government%20later%20decided%20to%20undo%20this%20change.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1703149440000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2019-05%2F51qsbfd_election-commission-reuters_62