0newspapers%2C%20registered%20with%20the%20Registrar%20of%20Newspapers%20for%20India%20(RNI)%20as%20of%20March%2031%2C%202019.%20The%20number%20subsequently%20rose%20to%201%2C43%2C423%20in%202020%2C%201%2C44%2C520%20in%202021%2C%201%2C46%2C045%20in%202022%2C%20and%201%2C48%2C363%20in%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUttar%20Pradesh%20tops%20the%20list%20with%2021%2C660%20periodicals%20registered%20with%20the%20government%2C%20followed%20by%20Maharashtra%20with%2020%2C448%20periodicals%2C%20and%20Delhi%20with%2016%2C446%20periodicals%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fscroll.in%2Flatest%2F1060852%2Fcentre-says-it-spent-rs-967-46-crore-on-print-advertisements-since-2019%5C%22%3Eaccording%20to%3Cem%3E%20Scroll.in%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1703079029000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F02%2F16132603%2FScreen-Shot-2020-02-16-at-1.25.49-PM.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fcentre-spent-rs-967-46-crore-for-publicity-of-govt-schemes-in-print-media-from-2019-to-2023%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20information%20was%20disclosed%20by%20Union%20information%20and%20broadcasting%20minister%2C%20Anurag%20Thakur%2C%20in%20Lok%20Sabha%20in%20response%20to%20a%20question%20seeking%20details%20on%20government%20advertisements%20in%20print%20media.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A7%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fcentre-spent-rs-967-46-crore-for-publicity-of-govt-schemes-in-print-media-from-2019-to-2023%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Roman%20Abramovich%20loses%20appeal%20against%20EU's%20Ukraine%20sanctions%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1703077860000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fe3.365dm.com%2F23%2F12%2F768x432%2Fskynews-roman-abramovich-chelsea_6399177.jpg%3F20231220131859%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Froman-abramovich-russian-former-chelsea-owner-loses-appeal-against-eus-ukraine-sanctions-13034850%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Roman%20Abramovich%2C%20the%20Russian%20billionaire%20and%20former%20Chelsea%20owner%2C%20has%20criticised%20the%20EU%20for%20rejecting%20his%20challenge%20to%20the%20sanctions%20it%20imposed%20on%20him%20after%20the%20invasion%20of%20Ukraine.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A13%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Froman-abramovich-russian-former-chelsea-owner-loses-appeal-against-eus-ukraine-sanctions-13034850%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews-sky-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Froman-abramovich-russian-former-chelsea-owner-loses-appeal-against-eus-ukraine-sanctions-13034850%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Froman-abramovich-russian-former-chelsea-owner-loses-appeal-against-eus-ukraine-sanctions-13034850%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22IMF%20Warns%20India%20on%20Debt%20Concerns%2C%20Says%20It%20May%20Exceed%20100%25%20of%20GDP%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F02%2F01025517%2F16953090889_059d966c4e_k.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20The%20International%20Monetary%20Fund%20(IMF)%20has%20warned%20that%20India%E2%80%99s%20general%20government%20debt%20may%20exceed%20100%25%20of%20gross%20domestic%20product%20(GDP)%20in%20the%20medium%20term%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Feconomy%2Fnews%2Fimf-cautions-india-on-govt-debt-vulnerabilities-centre-disagrees-123121901166_1.html%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EBusiness%20Standard%3C%2Fem%3E%20reported%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20saying%20that%20long-term%20risks%20are%20high%20because%20the%20country%20needs%20considerable%20investment%20to%20improve%20resilience%20to%20climate%20stresses%20and%20natural%20disasters.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThis%20suggests%20that%20new%20and%20preferably%20concessional%20sources%20of%20financing%20are%20needed%2C%20as%20well%20as%20greater%20private%20sector%20investment%20and%20carbon%20pricing%20or%20equivalent%20mechanism%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20IMF%20said%20in%20its%20annual%20Article%20IV%20consultation%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20IMF%20report%20is%20part%20of%20the%20Fund%E2%80%99s%20surveillance%20function%20under%20the%20Articles%20of%20Agreement%20with%20member%20countries.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Indian%20government%2C%20however%2C%20disagreed%2C%20saying%20that%20sovereign%20debt%20risks%20are%20limited%20as%20it%20is%20mainly%20denominated%20in%20domestic%20currency%2C%20the%20business%20daily%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EK.V.%20Subramanian%2C%20India%E2%80%99s%20executive%20director%20at%20the%20IMF%2C%20said%20the%20IMF%E2%80%99s%20assertion%20that%20the%20baseline%20carries%20the%20risk%20that%20debt%20would%20exceed%20100%25%20of%20GDP%20in%20the%20medium%20term%20in%20the%20event%20of%20shocks%20which%20India%20has%20experienced%20historically%20sounds%20extreme.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20same%20can%20be%20said%20of%20the%20staff%20prognosis%20that%20debt%20sustainability%20risks%20are%20high%20in%20the%20long%20term.%20The%20risks%20from%20sovereign%20debt%20are%20very%20limited%20as%20it%20is%20predominantly%20denominated%20in%20domestic%20currency.%20Despite%20the%20multitude%20of%20shocks%2C%20the%20global%20economy%20has%20faced%20in%20the%20past%20two%20decades%2C%20India%E2%80%99s%20public%20debt-to-GDP%20ratio%20at%20the%20general%20government%20level%20has%20barely%20increased%20from%2081%25%20in%202005-06%20to%2084%25%20in%202021-22%2C%20and%20back%20to%2081%25%20in%202022-23%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said%20in%20a%20statement%2C%20which%20is%20part%20of%20the%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20IMF%20also%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbanking%2Fimf-indian-currency-rbi%5C%22%3Ereclassified%3C%2Fa%3E%20India%E2%80%99s%20exchange%20rate%20regime%20to%20%E2%80%9Cstabilised%20arrangement%2C%E2%80%9D%20but%20India%20disputes%20this%2C%20emphasising%20the%20importance%20of%20exchange%20rate%20flexibility.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20its%20Article%20IV%20report%2C%20the%20IMF%20gave%20a%20fairly%20optimistic%20outlook%20for%20India%E2%80%99s%20economy%2C%20saying%20it%20has%20the%20potential%20to%20grow%20faster%20than%20the%20fund%E2%80%99s%20forecast%20of%206.3%25%20in%20the%20current%20and%20next%20fiscal%20years%20if%20the%20government%20undertakes%20key%20structural%20reforms%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bloomberg.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2F2023-12-20%2Fmodi-says-india-looking-into-us-allegations-of-murder-plot-ft%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EBloomberg%3C%2Fem%3E%20reported.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20an%20accompanying%20statement%20to%20its%20report%2C%20IMF%20said%20that%20India%20needs%20%E2%80%9Cambitious%E2%80%9D%20fiscal%20consolidation%20over%20the%20medium%20term%20in%20order%20to%20curb%20its%20public%20debt.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CA%20sharp%20global%20growth%20slowdown%20in%20the%20near%20term%20would%20affect%20India%20through%20trade%20and%20financial%20channels.%20Further%20global%20supply%20disruptions%20could%20cause%20recurrent%20commodity%20price%20volatility%2C%20increasing%20fiscal%20pressures%20for%20India.%20Domestically%2C%20weather%20shocks%20could%20reignite%20inflationary%20pressures%20and%20prompt%20further%20food%20export%20restrictions.%20On%20the%20upside%2C%20stronger%20than%20expected%20consumer%20demand%20and%20private%20investment%20would%20raise%20growth%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESteps%20to%20bring%20down%20public%20debt%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20October%202023%2C%20finance%20minister%C2%A0Nirmala%20Sitharaman%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livemint.com%2Feconomy%2Flooking-at-steps-to-bring-down-public-debt-sitharaman-11697820374098.html%5C%22%3Ehad%20said%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20government%20is%20looking%20at%20ways%20to%20bring%20down%20government%20debt%20and%20is%20monitoring%20the%20debt%20reduction%20measures%20taken%20by%20emerging%20market%20economies.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20central%20government%E2%80%99s%20debt%20stood%20at%20Rs%20155.6%20trillion%2C%20or%2057.1%25%20of%20GDP%2C%20at%20the%20end%20of%20March%202023.%20During%20the%20same%20period%2C%20the%20debt%20of%20state%20governments%20stood%20at%20about%2028%25%20of%20GDP%2C%20%3Cem%3EMint%3C%2Fem%3E%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20faces%20challenges%20in%20enhancing%20its%20credit%20ratings%20due%20to%20elevated%20debt%20levels%20and%20the%20substantial%20cost%20associated%20with%20servicing%20that%20debt.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDespite%20being%20called%20%E2%80%98bright%20spot%E2%80%99%20in%20the%20global%20economy%2C%20the%20Indian%20economy%20seems%20to%20be%20just%20carrying%20on%20in%20terms%20of%20sovereign%20investment%20ratings.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20June%202023%2C%20the%20%3Cem%3EEconomic%20Times%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feconomictimes.indiatimes.com%2Fnews%2Feconomy%2Findicators%2Findia-is-a-bright-spot-why-foreign-rating-agencies-cant-see-that%2Farticleshow%2F101014706.cms%5C%22%3Ehad%20written%3C%2Fa%3E%20about%20why%20all%20three%20global%20rating%20agencies%2C%20namely%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.deccanherald.com%2Fbusiness%2Ffitch-retain-indias-sovereign-rating-at-bbb-flags-deficits-govt-debt-1217073.html%5C%22%3EFitch%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Findia-firms-deleveraging-to-slow-down-little-room-for-rating-upgrade-s-p-123070400270_1.html%5C%22%3ES%26amp%3BP%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livemint.com%2Fnews%2Findia%2Fmoodys-affirms-india-s-baa3-rating-flags-risks-from-high-debt-burden-and-political-curbs-11692379545797.html%5C%22%3EMoody%E2%80%99s%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20have%20the%20lowest%20investment-grade%20rating%20on%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAgencies%20believe%20that%20India%E2%80%99s%20stronger%20fundamentals%20are%20undermined%20by%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20weak%20fiscal%20performance%20and%20burdensome%20debt%20stock%2C%20as%20well%20as%20the%20economy%E2%80%99s%20low%20GDP%20per%20capita%2C%20the%20business%20daily%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%E2%80%99s%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Findia-per-capita-income-gdp-growth%5C%22%3Eper%20capita%20income%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20nominal%20terms%20doubled%20to%20Rs%201%2C72%2C000%20since%202014-15%20when%20the%20Narendra%20Modi-led%20NDA%20came%20to%20power.%20That%20said%2C%20uneven%20income%20distribution%20remains%20a%20challenge%2C%20exacerbated%20by%20the%20Covid-19%20pandemic%20which%20gave%20rise%20to%20the%20%E2%80%98K-shaped%E2%80%99%20growth%20phenomenon.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20experts%2C%20India%E2%80%99s%20low%20per%20capita%20income%20is%20a%20major%20factor%20that%20pulls%20down%20India%E2%80%99s%20score%20in%20the%20sovereign%20rating.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20others%20say%20that%20the%20rating%20agencies%20should%20take%20into%20account%20that%20the%20quality%20of%20government%20expenditure%20has%20been%20improving.%20This%20will%20help%20in%20improving%20economic%20growth%2C%20through%20a%20stronger%20multiplier%20effect.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1703077217000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F02%2F01025517%2F16953090889_059d966c4e_k.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fimf-warns-india-on-debt-concerns-says-it-may-exceed-100-of-gdp-centre-disagrees%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20IMF%20said%20that%20long-term%20risks%20are%20high%20because%20the%20country%20needs%20considerable%20investment%20to%20improve%20resilience%20to%20climate%20stresses%20and%20natural%20disasters.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A88%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fimf-warns-india-on-debt-concerns-says-it-may-exceed-100-of-gdp-centre-disagrees%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22As%20the%20Indian%20Parliament%20Gags%2C%20Suspends%20and%20Expels%20Itself%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F20163108%2FGBxPF8iXUAAYdjW.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20functioning%20of%20Parliament%20is%20not%20to%20govern%20but%20to%20criticise.%20Its%20criticism%2C%20too%2C%20is%20directed%20not%20so%20much%20towards%20a%20fundamental%20modification%20of%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20policy%20as%20towards%20the%20education%20of%20public%20opinion.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E~Ivor%20Jennings%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIvor%20Jennings%E2%80%99%20apt%20formulation%2C%20made%20in%201939%2C%20starkly%20reflects%20how%20an%20errant%20Indian%20Parliament%20has%20become%20non-functional%20with%20logjams%2C%20gagging%2C%20suspensions%20and%20expulsions.%20Let%20alone%20dereliction%20in%20criticising%2C%20i%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Et%20does%20not%20even%20fit%20Thomas%20Carlyle%E2%80%99s%20description%20of%20the%20British%20House%20of%20Commons%20as%20a%20talking%20shop.%20In%20the%20ongoing%20winter%20session%20of%20parliament%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fcost-of-suspending-members-of-parliament%5C%22%3E143%20MPs%20have%20so%20far%20been%20suspended%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20reflecting%20a%20resolute%20and%20coordinated%20ousting%20of%20the%20opposition%20which%20perilously%20challenges%20Indian%20democracy.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFormer%20British%20prime%20minister%20Anthony%20Eden%20(1955-57)%20commented%20in%201960%2C%20%E2%80%9C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EOf%20all%20the%20experiments%20in%20government%2C%20which%20have%20been%20attempted%20since%20the%20beginning%20of%20the%20time%2C%20I%20believe%20that%20the%20Indian%20venture%20into%20parliamentary%20government%20is%20the%20most%20exciting%E2%80%9D%2C%20meaning%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eit%20began%20well.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EJawaharlal%20Nehru%20had%20underlined%20that%20the%20%E2%80%9Cparliamentary%20system%20requires%20not%20only%20stout%20opposition%2C%20not%20only%20forceful%20expression%20of%20opinions%20and%20views%20but%20an%20essential%20basis%20of%20cooperation%20between%20the%20opposition%20and%20the%20government%E2%80%9D.%20W.H.%20Morris-Jones%20stressed%20that%20parliaments%20introduced%20a%20new%20element%20of%20representation%20in%20government.%20That%20implies%20representation%20by%20both%20the%20government%20and%20the%20opposition.%20The%20principle%20must%20be%20respected%20by%20the%20presiding%20officers%20running%20the%20affairs%20of%20elected%20bodies.%20Obviously%2C%20the%20representative%20body%20of%201.4%20billion%20people%20is%20now%20severely%20remiss%20in%20performing%20its%20basic%20function.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EClaiming%20the%20origin%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20the%20UK%2C%20points%20out%20Morris-Jones%2C%20parliaments%20appeared%20four%20centuries%20before%20any%20notion%20of%20democracy%20began%20to%20emerge.%20Normally%2C%20the%20model%20parliament%20summoned%20in%201295%20by%20King%20Edward%20I%20is%20considered%20the%20beginning%20of%20parliament%2C%20though%20it%20was%20not%20democratically%20elected.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20foundation%20of%20the%20Westminster%20parliamentary%20system%20in%20India%20is%20inspired%20by%20the%20experience%20with%20the%20British-initiated%20elected%20bodies%20with%20limited%20representation%2C%20the%20Constituent%20Assembly%20noted%20it%20unambiguously.%20Recent%20Indian%20researches%2C%20however%2C%20claim%20Indian%20parliamentary%20traditions%20to%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ESabha%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3Es%20and%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ESamiti%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3Es%20of%20the%20Vedic%20and%20post-Vedic%20periods.%20These%20two%20bodies%20had%20a%20significant%20influence%20on%20the%20decision-making%20by%20the%20kings%2C%20who%20many%20a%20time%20were%20elected.%20The%20Rigved%20even%20prescribed%20that%20a%20king%20needed%20to%20be%20accepted%20and%20respected%20only%20if%20he%20worked%20in%20the%20public%20interest.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAurobindo%20said%20Manu%20laid%20down%20that%20an%20unjust%20and%20oppressive%20king%20should%20be%20killed%20by%20his%20own%20subjects%20like%20a%20mad%20dog.%20The%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EArthashastra%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20argues%20that%20the%20King%20on%20coronation%20took%20an%20oath%20to%20serve%20the%20people%20and%20he%20used%20to%20abide%20by%20the%20assemblies.%20Nehru%20argues%20in%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EGlimpses%20of%20World%20History%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20that%20there%20was%20no%20divine%20right%20of%20kings%2C%20no%20autocratic%20power.%20And%20if%20the%20king%20misbehaved%2C%20his%20people%20had%20the%20right%20to%20remove%20him%20and%20put%20another%20in%20his%20place.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ENitisara%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20of%20Shukracharya%20comments%2C%20%E2%80%9CPublic%20opinion%20is%20more%20powerful%20than%20the%20king%20as%20the%20rope%20made%20of%20many%20fibers%20is%20strong%20enough%20to%20drag%20a%20lion%E2%80%9D%2C%20said%20Nehru.%20The%20rise%20of%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Eganarajya%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20as%20a%20system%20of%20government%20in%20the%20post-Vedic%20period%20is%20cited%20as%20the%20precursor%20of%20the%20parliamentary%20tradition%20in%20India.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EGrammar%20of%20anarchy%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20systematic%20bedlam%20of%20today%2C%20a%20systemic%20aberration%2C%20begs%20the%20question%20if%20we%20are%20running%20the%20system%20well%20enough%20for%20the%20electorate.%20The%20role%20of%20the%20government%20of%20the%20day%2C%20which%20calls%20the%20shots%3B%20the%20opposition%2C%20which%20is%20unprepared%20in%20substance%20and%20comes%20prepared%20to%20play%20to%20the%20gallery%20in%20the%20era%20of%20electronic%20media%20exposure%2C%20are%20both%20responsible.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3ESushma%20Swaraj%2C%20a%20two-time%20NDA%20Union%20minister%2C%20admitted%20in%202011%20that%20various%20state%20units%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fnews%2Fnational%2Fsushma-bjp-state-units-pressure-us-to-get-parliament-adjourned%2Farticle2348007.ece%5C%22%3Epressured%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20BJP%20parliamentary%20party%20to%20adjourn%20parliament%20and%20each%20day%20strategies%20would%20be%20made%20to%20stall%20its%20proceedings%20even%20without%20a%20definite%20issue.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EShekhar%20Gupta%20had%20observed%20that%20due%20to%20the%20BJP%20strategy%2C%20the%20UPA%20was%20sliding%20into%20paralysis%20and%20questioned%20if%20the%20opposition%20would%20want%20that%20to%20happen%20to%20the%20NDA.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EPartisan%20presiding%20officers%20complete%20the%20story%20of%20what%20B.R.%20Ambedkar%20warned%20the%20nation%20against%20in%20his%20penultimate%20day%20speech%20in%20the%20Constituent%20Assembly%20%E2%80%93%20turning%20the%20august%20institution%20into%20a%20%E2%80%98%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.outlookindia.com%2Fwebsite%2Fstory%2Fthe-grammar-of-anarchy%2F289235%5C%22%3Egrammar%20of%20anarchy%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhether%20or%20not%20other%20parties%20and%20leaders%20in%20opposition%20follow%20a%20similar%20organised%20strategy%20to%20disrupt%20parliament%2C%20it%20is%20happening%20regularly.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F20111531%2FUntitled-design-5.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F20111531%2FUntitled-design-5.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F20111531%2FUntitled-design-5-300x169.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F20111531%2FUntitled-design-5-1024x576.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-689963%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22675%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ESome%20of%20the%20141%20suspended%20MPs%20sit%20in%20protest%20outside%20parliament.%20Photo%3A%20Video%20screengrab%2FX%2F%40KBanerjee_AITC%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EThe%20presiding%20officers%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ELet%20alone%20negotiating%20a%20strategy%20with%20the%20opposition%20benches%20for%20smooth%20functioning%2C%20the%20presiding%20officers%20of%20the%20two%20houses%20are%20summarily%20suspending%20the%20members%20for%20the%20entire%20session.%20Obviously%2C%20the%20impartial%20and%20efficacious%20conduct%20of%20the%20proceedings%20of%20the%20houses%20is%20in%20peril.%20Are%20the%20chairman%20of%20the%20Rajya%20Sabha%20(vice%20president%20of%20India)%20and%20the%20speaker%20of%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20playing%20partisan%20cards%3F%20The%20Westminster%20tradition%20of%20the%20speaker%20of%20the%20House%20of%20Commons%20resigning%20from%20her%2Fhis%20party%20has%20not%20been%20followed%20in%20India.%20Yet%2C%20G.V.%20Mavalankar%2C%20M.A.%20Ayyangar%20and%20Hukum%20Singh%20left%20healthy%20precedents%20behind%20them.%20Indira%20Gandhi%20opted%20for%20partisanship.%20Partisanship%20by%20both%20the%20presiding%20officers%20has%20been%20pushed%20beyond%20all%20limits%20today.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EObviously%2C%20the%20analysis%20does%20not%20include%20the%20first%20Modi%20term%20reflecting%20the%20extent%20of%20partisanship%20of%20the%20chairs.%20Rajya%20Sabha%20chairman%20Jagdeep%20Dhankar%20is%20frequently%20on%20his%20feet%20reprimanding%20the%20opposition%20MPs%20and%20instantly%20expunging%20their%20remarks%3B%20forgetting%20the%20dignity%20of%20his%20office.%20Such%20a%20sight%20does%20not%20present%20a%20healthy%20picture%20of%20parliamentary%20functioning%20in%20India.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20Read%20%7C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fcost-of-suspending-members-of-parliament%5C%22%3EOver%2014%20Crore%20Voters%20Without%20a%20Voice%20in%20Lok%20Sabha%3A%20Calculating%20the%20Cost%20of%20Suspending%20MPs%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EExpulsions%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EExpulsion%20of%20an%20elected%20member%20from%20either%20house%20is%20an%20extreme%20measure%20and%20if%20not%20done%20prudently%2C%20it%20shows%20a%20brazen%20disregard%20of%20the%20popular%20will.%20It%20is%20apposite%20here%20to%20recall%20the%20first%20such%20controversy%20from%20the%20provisional%20Parliament%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Findia%2Fhow-an-mp-was-expelled-for-similar-scandal%2Farticleshow%2F1331144.cms%5C%22%3EH.G.%20Mudgal%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20the%20Congress%20party%20in%201951.%20Uncomfortable%20at%20the%20complaint%20that%20Mudgal%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Ehad%20taken%20Rs%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E1%2C000%20each%20on%20two%20occasions%20from%20the%20Bullion%20Merchants%E2%80%99%20Association%20to%20ask%20questions%20in%20parliament%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3ENehru%20constituted%20a%20committee%20to%20investigate%20and%20forwarded%20its%20recommendation%20indicting%20him%20to%20speaker%20Mavalankar.%20However%2C%20finding%20his%20expulsion%20imminent%2C%20Mudgal%20resigned.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20recent%20expulsion%20of%20opposition%20Lok%20Sabha%20MP%20Mahua%20Moitra%20has%20raised%20the%20eyebrows%20of%20constitutional%20experts.%20An%20ardent%20critic%20of%20the%20regime%20and%20the%20prime%20minister%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EMoitra%20was%20expelled%20dubiously%20at%20the%20recommendation%20of%20the%20Parliamentary%20Ethics%20Committee%20for%20allegedly%20taking%20money%20to%20ask%20questions.%20She%20has%20moved%20the%20apex%20court%2C%20which%20will%20hear%20her%20plea%20in%20January%202024.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EThe%20road%20ahead%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20current%20commotion%2C%20and%20subsequent%20mass%20suspensions%2C%20is%20due%20to%20the%20demand%20of%20the%20opposition%20for%20a%20statement%20by%20Union%20home%20minister%20Amit%20Shah%20regarding%20a%20security%20lapse%20when%20two%20men%20entered%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20and%20opened%20smoke%20cannisters.%20While%20the%20police%20are%20weaving%20a%20terror%20case%20against%20those%20who%20are%20responsible%20for%20the%20breach%2C%20the%20protesting%20MPs%20are%20suspended%20for%20demanding%20a%20statement%20from%20the%20home%20minister!%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThere%20are%20less%20than%20six%20months%20before%20the%20general%20election%20in%20May%202024.%20Following%20massive%20electoral%20victories%20in%20three%20north%20Indian%20states%2C%20the%20BJP%20is%20self-assured%20about%20returning%20to%20power.%20However%2C%20the%20road%20ahead%20for%20India%E2%80%99s%20parliamentary%20democracy%20appears%20rugged%20and%20bumpy.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cspan%3EAjay%20K.%20Mehra%20is%20a%20political%20scientist.%20He%20was%20Atal%20Bihari%20Vajpayee%20Senior%20Fellow%2C%20Nehru%20Memorial%20Museum%20and%20Library%2C%20New%20Delhi%2C%202019-21%20and%20Principal%2C%20Shaheed%20Bhagat%20Singh%20Evening%20College%2C%20Delhi%20University%20(2018).%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1703075410000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F20163108%2FGBxPF8iXUAAYdjW.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Findian-parliament-gags-suspends-and-expels-itself%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%2